    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 8,
                            1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In accordance with a request made to me by the
                        governor-general of Canada, acting under instructions from Her Majesty’s
                        Government, I have the honor to transmit herewith, for the information of
                        the United States Government, a copy of a minute<note n="2" xml:id="d207fn2">See Senate Ex. Doc. No. 67, Fifty-third Congress, third session, page
                            122.</note> of his excellency’s council, dated the 16th ultimo, to which
                        is appended a complete list of such British vessels as have cleared from
                        Canadian ports for the sealing grounds during the present season.</p>
                <p>Of these vessels it appears that 34 have cleared for the coast of Japan and
                        24 for the American coast, making in all 48.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
